  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Of the city&rsquo;s total expense budget for one year, the city budgeted <span class=\"italic\">y</span> million dollars for departmental expenses and 201 million dollars for all other expenses. This means that the expression <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y plus 201\"></span> represents the total expense budget, in millions of dollars, for one year. It&rsquo;s given that the total expense budget for one year is <span class=\"italic\">x</span> million dollars. It follows then that the expression <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y plus 201\"></span> is equivalent to <span class=\"italic\">x</span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y plus 201, equals x\"></span>. Subtracting <span class=\"italic\">y</span> from both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"201 equals, x minus y\"></span>. By the symmetric property of equality, this is the same as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x minus y, equals 201\"></span>.<p>Choices A and C are incorrect. Because it&rsquo;s given that the total expense budget for one year, <span class=\"italic\">x</span> million dollars, is comprised of the departmental expenses, <span class=\"italic\">y</span> million dollars, and all other expenses, 201 million dollars, the expressions <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x plus y\"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x minus y  \"></span> both must be equivalent to a value greater than 201 million dollars. Therefore, the equations <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x plus y, equals 201 \"></span>and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 x minus y, equals 201 \"></span>aren&rsquo;t true. Choice D is incorrect. The value of <span class=\"italic\">x </span>must be greater than the value of <span class=\"italic\">y</span>. Therefore, <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y minus x, equals 201\"></span> can&rsquo;t represent this relationship.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
